            <pb/>
            <hi rend="italic">Religion in Australia.</hi>–An Act of Council has
                    <lb/>passed to the effect, that whenever t300 are raised <lb/>for the erection
                    of a church and parsonage, the Go<lb break="no"/>vernment may advance the same
                    sum–and that if one <lb/>hundred adults sign a declaration of their wish
                    for <lb/>a clergyman, a salary of t100 may be given–if two <lb/>hundred a
                    salary of t150, and if five hundred, a <lb/>salary of t200. Already nine
                    clergyman are wanted.</p>
